    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-09T00:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-09T00:30:00-05:00" n="599"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/1415: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Officer in Charge at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-09T11:00:00+05:30"
                            >August 9, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 9—6:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>581. Gandhi,<note n="31" xml:id="d599fn31">Mohandas K. Gandhi, leader of civil
                        disobedience movement in India.</note> Nehru,<note n="32" xml:id="d599fn32"
                        >Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru, Congress Party leader; associated with Gandhi in
                        opposition to British rule in India.</note> Azad,<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d599fn33">Maulana Azad, President of the Congress Party.</note> and
                    about 20 other Congress leaders were arrested early this morning (reference my
                    580, August 8, 7 p.m.<note n="34" xml:id="d599fn34">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_708">p.
                    708</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <p>Speaking before All India Congress Committee last night Gandhi stated that he
                    would make every effort to see Viceroy<note n="35" xml:id="d599fn35">Marquess of
                        Linlithgow.</note> before launching struggle but Government was apparently
                    unimpressed by this statement.</p>
                <p>There is as yet no news as to whether, in view of foregoing, movement will be
                    started forthwith.</p>
                <pb facs="0724" n="712" xml:id="pg_712"/>
                <p>The Indian defense member confirmed to me last night the explanation given in the
                    last paragraph of telegram referred to above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
